############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML For your college interview, you must wear a tie. You own 3 regular (boring) ties and 5 (cool) bow ties. a. How many choices do you have for your neck-wear?
[_____]{8}
a. You realize that the interview is for clown college, so you should probably wear both a regular tie and a bow tie. How many choices do you have now?
[_____]{15}
a. For the rest of your outfit, you have 5 shirts, 4 skirts, 3 pants, and 7 dresses. You want to select either a shirt to wear with a skirt or pants, or just a dress. How many outfits do you have to choose from?
[_____]{42}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. 8 ties. Use the additive principle.
a. 15 ties. Use the multiplicative principle a. [`5\cdot (4+3) + 7 = 42`] outfits.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
