############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML A pizza parlor offers 10 toppings. a. How many 3-topping pizzas could they put on their menu? Assume double toppings are not allowed.
[_____]{$ans1}
a. How many total pizzas are possible, with between zero and ten toppings (but not double toppings) allowed?
[_____]{$ans2}
a. The pizza parlor will list the 10 toppings in two equal-sized columns on their menu. How many ways can they arrange the toppings in the left column?
[_____]{$ans3}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
